CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 11, 1958, pg. A19 reads: " Celebrate 45th Anniversary - Mr. and Mrs. James Gray of N. St. Clair St., celebrated their 45th wedding anniversary last week by entertaining relatives and friends at their home at dinner. Some of the guests who attended included the Jesse Harveys; sons, Kenneth and James Holmes; daughter, Dorothy Jackson, and sons. Clarence and Daryle; the Henry Lees, Mmes. James McCoy, Carrie Young, Fannie Moncrief, Zara Docekins, Bessie Roach; the Misses Myrtid Earl and Barbara Goggins, the Harrison Williamses, the Henry Hills, the Rhodes Dearrings and daughter from Cincinnati, the Chester Lees and sons, the Lonnie Lees and sons and Mrs. Hill and Son, all of Cleveland. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of guests of Mr. and Mrs. James Gray during their 45th wedding anniversary celebration, including Mr. and Mrs. Jesse Harvey, Kenneth Gray, son; James Holmes, son; Dorothy Jackson, daughter with sons Clarence and Daryle; Mr. and Mrs. Henry Lee, Mrs. James McCoy, Carrie Young, Fannie Moncrief, Zara Docekins, Bessie Roach; Myrtid Earl, Barbara Goggins, Mr. and Mrs. Harrison Williams, Mr. and Mrs. Henry Hill, Mr. and Mrs. Rhodes Dearring and daughter, Mr. and Mrs. Chester Lee and sons, Mr. and Mrs. Lonnie Lee and sons, and Mrs. Hill and son, in home on N. St. Clair St.
